You as a Data Scientist (Insight and Analytics) will:
Leverage your knowledge of statistical methods and applications; expertise with data mining tools and techniques; and advanced analytical ability to derive actionable insights from big data;
Design and implement algorithms and predictive models – from prototype to production - to solve critical business problems while developing data mining architectures, coding standards, statistical reporting, and data analysis methodologies;
Analyze large and complex data-sets to identify meaningful patterns that deliver insight;
Work with cross-departmental teams to identify high-value use scenarios that are amenable to an analytics solution;
Assist with the creation of informative visualizations that intuitively displays large amounts of data and/or complex relationships;
Work closely with other IT professionals to identify, design, build, and maintain appropriate data-sets for complex experiments.
Is this the right role for you?
Graduate or post-graduate university degree in Computer Science, Mathematics or Statistics, Engineering or equivalent. Plus 2-4 years of relevant work experience;
Extensive experience solving analytical problems using quantitative approaches;
Comfort manipulating and analyzing complex, high-volume, high dimensionality data from varying sources. Experience with very large datasets. Familiarity with relational, SQL, and NoSQL databases;
Expert knowledge of statistical analysis tools such as R, Matlab, Python or equivalent. Fluency with scripting languages such as Python or other.

EllisDon is proud to provide this unique career opportunity within a progressive environment with continuous learning and opportunity for growth, as well as a competitive compensation package.

Go ahead and be yourself. We'll pay you for it!
