POSITION OVERVIEW
As the Environmental Scientist, you are responsible for the safe completion of field work programs, data management
and preparation of factual reports under the direction of an Environmental Lead Scientist or Environmental Project

Manager. You deliver excellent client service and build confidence in your relationships through solid decision making

abilities. This position supports Remediation, Reclamation or Natural Sciences projects located in Northeast, BC.

and includes significant field work activities.
Specifically, you will
Lead the investigation, remediation, reclamation or natural sciences field activities in accordance with
regulatory requirements and SynergyAspen’s preferred operating procedures;
Provide technical report writing;
Assist with preparation of scopes of work, and cost estimates;
Adhere to client-specific and SynergyAspen’s Health and Safety policies and a commitment to health and
safety as an integral component of all activities;
Ensure timely delivery of assigned tasks;
Provide high quality data, safely and on time;
Provide excellent customer service to clients, maintaining a positive, cooperative attitude when working
alone or as part of a team.

Qualifications Requirements
Candidates with an A.Ag. or P.Ag. designation preferred;
Two year Technical Diploma or Degree in Environmental Sciences;
Experience with pipeline and/or construction monitoring, ALR soils, vegetation, reclamation, and erosion
control;
Must have field experience in Northeastern BC and be available to work in the Fort St. John area and
possibly alternate locations, as needed;
Four to six years related remediation/reclamation/natural sciences field experience preferred, but not
mandatory;
Possess clean driving record and able to provide acceptable driver’s abstract;
Good oral and written communication skills, attention to detail;
Proficient with Microsoft suite and using database programs;
Must be able to work in a safe and responsible manner at all times.
