At Golder, we thrive on challenges.
Golder is not just a place to work, it is a promise of a living, dynamic environment where people collaborate, innovate, build enduring relationships, excel, and grow professionally in a strong culture of ownership.

Do you have the desire to learn? The drive to excel and thrive in an engaged, collaborative environment?

Golder has a new opportunity for a Drafter to assist the professional and technical staff working for a major oil & gas client on contract basis based in Windsor, Ontario.

Responsibilities include:

Collaborating with project scientists and engineers to provide a variety of figures using Excel and AutoCAD including:

Site maps from topographic data and survey field notes;
Key plans, site plans, site design drawings and cross-sections;
Groundwater flow diagrams, including performing various calculations;
Managing workload commitments by following an established workflow and data management process;

Preparing various types of borehole logs, using specific logging software;

Taking responsibility for product quality control by adhering to company standards and procedures and paying diligent attention in both the creation of draft figures and any edits necessary for finalization.

You have to possess the following qualifications:

A technical diploma or industry-recognized training in AutoCAD and other relevant software;
